cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a new class-based concurrent object-oriented language and formalizes its syntax, semantics, and type system. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper introduces usage types, which are used to formalize protocols associated with classes and specify the available methods, tests clients must perform on the result of methods, and the object status. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper addresses the issue of verifying client code adherence against the sought class behavior, which is a software engineering concern. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses concurrent programming and introduces a standard sync qualifier to prevent thread interference in certain operations on shared objects. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new language that enforces by static typing that methods are called only when available and by a single client if so specified in the usage type, which is related to data structures and algorithms.
